WEBVTT

00:02.490 --> 00:05.976
[AUDIO LOGO]

00:44.850 --> 00:45.880
Good afternoon.

00:45.880 --> 00:48.630
I'm reporting live from
the Katzman Cove Marina,

00:48.630 --> 00:50.670
site of where the
stolen painting is

00:50.670 --> 00:54.300
believed to be transported
from by three convicts.

00:54.300 --> 00:57.090
Most, if not all, have
reportedly been killed.

01:00.530 --> 01:02.180
Did you see that?

01:02.180 --> 01:03.050
I saw it too.

01:21.560 --> 01:22.790
The painting!

01:22.790 --> 01:25.400
While the painting has
not yet been recovered,

01:25.400 --> 01:29.300
some of the thieves have,
or at least parts of them.

01:29.300 --> 01:30.360
Yes, parts.

01:35.830 --> 01:38.170
It is believed that
a man-eating shark

01:38.170 --> 01:41.350
has been roaming these waters
and may have attacked the group

01:41.350 --> 01:43.720
as they traversed the
cove to go and hide

01:43.720 --> 01:45.310
the painting on Cat Island.

01:53.690 --> 01:55.020
What the hell?

02:05.864 --> 02:08.329
[GASPING]

02:08.329 --> 02:11.780
[SHARK GROWLING]

02:22.133 --> 02:25.420
OK, Stan, this will be part
two of our location piece.

02:25.420 --> 02:27.340
Just split the segments
up with a commercial

02:27.340 --> 02:28.670
when you edit them together.

02:28.670 --> 02:29.260
You got it.

02:32.530 --> 02:33.400
The ocean.

02:33.400 --> 02:36.820
Behind me it looks
inviting, serene, and safe.

02:36.820 --> 02:37.870
But is it?

02:37.870 --> 02:41.110
We have received several reports
of a shark prowling the shores,

02:41.110 --> 02:43.480
and while this isn't
uncommon, these reports

02:43.480 --> 02:46.600
claim that the shark is
in fact monstrous, ranging

02:46.600 --> 02:49.570
from 50 to 60 feet
in length, larger

02:49.570 --> 02:51.070
than any known great white.

02:51.070 --> 02:52.810
Does the sudden
appearance have anything

02:52.810 --> 02:55.450
to do with the increased
drilling at the newly renovated

02:55.450 --> 02:56.980
rig just offshore?

02:56.980 --> 03:00.100
The EPA is still trying
to get accurate reports

03:00.100 --> 03:01.990
on just how far
they are drilling

03:01.990 --> 03:04.570
and at what cost to the
environment this will have.

03:04.570 --> 03:07.690
Is the rig hiding a secret,
and is there any connection

03:07.690 --> 03:11.608
to the mysterious monster
supposedly prowling the depths?

03:11.608 --> 03:15.094
[MUSIC PLAYING]

05:47.300 --> 05:48.420
(SINGING) It ain't you.

05:48.420 --> 05:52.462
I knew it couldn't be true
because we can't [INAUDIBLE]

05:52.462 --> 05:52.962
together.

05:52.962 --> 05:57.390
You don't understand my
moves, so don't expect me

05:57.390 --> 06:02.145
to [INAUDIBLE]
because we can't--

06:02.145 --> 06:04.200
To your right,
Bree, to your right.

06:04.200 --> 06:06.700
No, no, no, your other right.

06:06.700 --> 06:08.460
I'm doing my best.

06:08.460 --> 06:10.150
Well, your best
isn't good enough.

06:10.150 --> 06:11.950
You have to be perfect.

06:11.950 --> 06:14.670
I'm trying.

06:14.670 --> 06:16.460
You most certainly
are sometimes.

06:22.940 --> 06:23.980
Let's just take five.

06:30.510 --> 06:31.444
[PHONE RINGING]

06:40.058 --> 06:41.510
[SIGHS]

06:41.510 --> 06:43.190
Yeah.

06:43.190 --> 06:44.450
OK.

06:44.450 --> 06:46.760
Yeah, that's great.

06:46.760 --> 06:47.360
Super.

06:47.360 --> 06:48.115
All right.

06:48.115 --> 06:49.115
We'll be there tomorrow.

06:53.590 --> 06:56.050
That was Top Model Tomorrow.

06:56.050 --> 06:59.410
You have a video shoot in
the morning on a yacht.

06:59.410 --> 07:00.370
That's amazing.

07:00.370 --> 07:02.470
That show's going to
be seen by millions.

07:02.470 --> 07:03.340
Yeah.

07:03.340 --> 07:06.580
You can thank me later.

07:06.580 --> 07:10.060
So where's that photographer?

07:10.060 --> 07:12.083
Yo, Ansel Adams, you ready?

07:12.083 --> 07:14.500
(SINGING) Because she had a
lot of [INAUDIBLE] in a thong.

07:14.500 --> 07:16.780
Angel on my side telling
me I don't want it,

07:16.780 --> 07:19.370
the devil on the other
telling me to hop on it.

07:19.370 --> 07:22.620
I hop on it, now I
feel I'm sacrificing--

07:22.620 --> 07:24.570
[MUSICAL INTRO]

07:24.570 --> 07:27.060
Good evening, this
is News 6 at 5.

07:27.060 --> 07:29.880
Today's top story is the hunt
for the missing million dollar

07:29.880 --> 07:32.280
painting stolen
in a tragic heist

07:32.280 --> 07:35.280
by unknown and
presumably dead thieves.

07:35.280 --> 07:38.820
The painting, a one of a kind
rendition of Chinese Grauman

07:38.820 --> 07:41.610
Theater by noted
artist Yuri Otonatu,

07:41.610 --> 07:44.250
was stolen last
week, even though it

07:44.250 --> 07:46.950
was under close
scrutiny at the time.

07:46.950 --> 07:49.710
In the painting, we see the
famous theater and displays

07:49.710 --> 07:53.010
and marquee advertising for
the initial release of the film

07:53.010 --> 07:55.800
King Kong, a favorite
of the artist.

07:55.800 --> 07:58.230
After tracing the painting
to a local marina,

07:58.230 --> 08:00.570
authorities believe the
bandits were attempting

08:00.570 --> 08:03.450
to shuttle the stolen
goods across the channel

08:03.450 --> 08:08.250
to a small island two hours off
the coast called Cat Island.

08:08.250 --> 08:10.320
The trail, we are
told, has gone cold,

08:10.320 --> 08:12.810
with no sign of the
thieves or the painting.

08:12.810 --> 08:15.000
Authorities now believe
there is a connection

08:15.000 --> 08:18.540
between the tragic oil rig
explosion, the recent shark

08:18.540 --> 08:20.370
sightings, and the thieves.

08:20.370 --> 08:23.610
What that connection is
exactly is forthcoming.

08:23.610 --> 08:26.970
We will be airing a special
later tonight highlighting

08:26.970 --> 08:28.380
eyewitness accounts.

08:28.380 --> 08:29.640
Now for the weather.

08:29.640 --> 08:30.900
Oh, Jesus.

08:30.900 --> 08:32.470
This is not looking good.

08:32.470 --> 08:34.720
I think we have
ourselves a big problem.

08:34.720 --> 08:36.210
What's the problem, Clark?

08:36.210 --> 08:38.400
Yeah, the painting's
missing, but none of that

08:38.400 --> 08:40.140
can be traced back to us.

08:40.140 --> 08:42.179
Not yet anyways.

08:42.179 --> 08:46.380
I knew these guys were
going to bungle this job.

08:46.380 --> 08:50.130
All they had to do was
meet us on Cat Island,

08:50.130 --> 08:52.170
give us the painting,
they get their cut,

08:52.170 --> 08:54.060
and then we get our cut.

08:54.060 --> 08:56.010
It was simple.

08:56.010 --> 08:57.090
I'm hungry.

08:57.090 --> 08:59.260
Let's go down to the
pier and get some pizza.

08:59.260 --> 09:02.100
We've been hiding
[INAUDIBLE] for three days.

09:02.100 --> 09:04.840
Oh, you keep thinking
with that stomach, Gerald,

09:04.840 --> 09:08.640
and you're going to end
up like our friends.

09:08.640 --> 09:12.420
I hope not, but I am hungry.

09:12.420 --> 09:14.250
Boy, what do you think happened?

09:14.250 --> 09:16.650
Honestly?

09:16.650 --> 09:17.790
No, lie to me.

09:17.790 --> 09:20.040
Of course honestly.

09:20.040 --> 09:22.080
I don't think they
made it to Cat Island.

09:22.080 --> 09:25.050
We waited there for two
days thinking they'd show,

09:25.050 --> 09:28.320
and they didn't
contact us afterwards.

09:28.320 --> 09:30.240
Maybe they double crossed us.

09:30.240 --> 09:31.260
I don't think so.

09:31.260 --> 09:34.170
We knew their every move.

09:34.170 --> 09:37.230
That leaves only
one other option.

09:37.230 --> 09:39.080
Get some pizza.

09:39.080 --> 09:39.930
God.

09:39.930 --> 09:43.230
If I didn't promise your mother
I'd look after you, I swear.

09:43.230 --> 09:46.320
That renegade shark got
them and the painting

09:46.320 --> 09:48.450
sank to the bottom
of the channel.

09:48.450 --> 09:49.710
This is the map here.

09:49.710 --> 09:52.290
This is the marina.

09:52.290 --> 09:53.490
Here's Cat Island.

09:53.490 --> 09:56.670
This is the route they took.

09:56.670 --> 09:58.620
And with the debris
that was found,

09:58.620 --> 10:03.180
they went down
right about there.

10:03.180 --> 10:03.960
Huh.

10:03.960 --> 10:06.310
How deep do you think that is?

10:06.310 --> 10:10.020
Well, there's a channel and
the ocean tides can build up,

10:10.020 --> 10:12.900
but my guess, it's no
deeper than 20 feet,

10:12.900 --> 10:15.572
at least where we
have to search.

10:15.572 --> 10:16.320
All right.

10:16.320 --> 10:18.870
We'll get somebody to dive
in there once we find it.

10:18.870 --> 10:20.490
Without too much trouble, sure.

10:20.490 --> 10:23.550
And it might be more
shallow than I think.

10:23.550 --> 10:26.010
It'd be like finding a
needle in a haystack.

10:26.010 --> 10:26.655
Not exactly.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.130
What is that?

10:32.130 --> 10:34.350
This is a small
underwater camera that's

10:34.350 --> 10:35.970
attached to this monitor.

10:35.970 --> 10:36.870
We'll find it.

10:36.870 --> 10:38.550
It monitors everything.

10:38.550 --> 10:41.090
Hey, that'd be great
to use for fishing.

10:41.090 --> 10:42.690
Oh, we're going to
go fishing tomorrow

10:42.690 --> 10:44.457
morning, but not for fish.

10:44.457 --> 10:46.290
We're going to find
ourselves that painting.

10:49.870 --> 10:51.625
Can we get something
to eat first, please?

10:58.570 --> 10:59.740
What's this?

10:59.740 --> 11:01.660
Your assignment for tomorrow.

11:01.660 --> 11:02.800
No, no.

11:02.800 --> 11:03.980
Not going to happen.

11:03.980 --> 11:06.070
I'm not spending
all day on a boat

11:06.070 --> 11:09.160
with some bimbo model
for that limp dick show

11:09.160 --> 11:11.410
Top Model Tomorrow.

11:11.410 --> 11:13.000
Yes, you are.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.130
The boss already
assigned me to the marina

11:15.130 --> 11:17.440
for the shark and
oil rig disaster.

11:17.440 --> 11:18.550
Can't do it.

11:18.550 --> 11:22.120
Well, he thinks you're
so good at what you do,

11:22.120 --> 11:24.820
you can do all three.

11:24.820 --> 11:27.700
You're kidding, right?

11:27.700 --> 11:30.100
You're at least going along?

11:30.100 --> 11:31.960
I'm going to stay in
the studio to cover

11:31.960 --> 11:35.440
anything you find and
follow your little Top Model

11:35.440 --> 11:36.760
adventures.

11:36.760 --> 11:37.750
What a crock.

11:37.750 --> 11:39.460
I get seasick.

11:39.460 --> 11:42.460
Nice try.

11:42.460 --> 11:44.995
There's got to be a better way
to earn a living than this.

12:31.785 --> 12:33.980
You sure have a
lot of stuff there.

12:33.980 --> 12:36.000
We only need two outfit changes.

12:36.000 --> 12:36.530
I know.

12:36.530 --> 12:38.150
This is just in case.

12:38.150 --> 12:39.645
In case of what?

12:39.645 --> 12:40.145
Well--

12:42.730 --> 12:43.960
Well, spit it out, Bree.

12:43.960 --> 12:45.280
What?

12:45.280 --> 12:46.630
I'm afraid of the ocean.

12:46.630 --> 12:48.943
Can't we just stay
up on the dock?

12:48.943 --> 12:50.860
Don't worry, nothing's
going to happen to you.

12:50.860 --> 12:52.510
I will make sure of that.

12:52.510 --> 12:54.730
I'm not going to get
attacked by a shark?

12:54.730 --> 12:56.510
Why would you say such a thing?

12:56.510 --> 12:58.510
It's been all over the
news, some monster shark

12:58.510 --> 12:59.830
crawling the beaches.

12:59.830 --> 13:01.060
Balderdash.

13:01.060 --> 13:03.640
The news just exaggerates
to boost ratings.

13:03.640 --> 13:06.160
Sharks have lived in
these waters forever.

13:06.160 --> 13:08.260
That's where they
live, you know.

13:08.260 --> 13:10.690
I just don't want to
get attacked by a shark.

13:10.690 --> 13:13.330
Sharks don't instinctively
attack humans.

13:13.330 --> 13:16.400
They mistake them for
something else like a seal.

13:16.400 --> 13:18.100
Besides, we'll be on a yacht.

13:18.100 --> 13:20.500
What shark can swallow that?

13:20.500 --> 13:22.240
Yeah, you're right.

13:22.240 --> 13:23.210
I know I am.

13:23.210 --> 13:23.800
Now, come on.

13:31.000 --> 13:31.960
Good luck today.

13:31.960 --> 13:32.920
Whatever.

13:32.920 --> 13:34.540
We have to be live by noon.

13:34.540 --> 13:36.280
Other than that, I
can cut into your feet

13:36.280 --> 13:38.320
any time you think we
have something newsworthy.

13:38.320 --> 13:40.270
Yeah, my drowning.

13:40.270 --> 13:42.520
I just love your
positive attitude.

13:42.520 --> 13:43.390
Surf's up.

13:50.665 --> 13:52.120
[HONKS HORN]

13:54.060 --> 13:55.080
Come on, you idiot!

13:55.080 --> 13:55.950
Move it!

13:55.950 --> 13:57.063
I'm coming, I'm coming.

13:57.063 --> 13:57.563
Come on!

13:57.563 --> 13:58.270
I'm coming.

13:58.270 --> 13:58.510
God.

13:58.510 --> 13:58.865
Jesus!

13:58.865 --> 13:59.365
Move your--

13:59.365 --> 14:00.030
Jesus Christ.

14:00.030 --> 14:01.260
--stupid ass, will you?

14:01.260 --> 14:02.720
We've got a long
day ahead of us.

14:29.210 --> 14:34.160
Dock 7, row 6.

14:34.160 --> 14:38.300
Skip SE5, right over there.

14:59.770 --> 15:00.820
A yacht.

15:00.820 --> 15:01.900
Right.

15:01.900 --> 15:06.016
I should have known this
was going to be a cluster F.

15:06.016 --> 15:07.944
[GROWLING]

15:08.908 --> 15:09.870
What the hell?

15:33.260 --> 15:35.060
You better slow down.

15:35.060 --> 15:38.420
The last thing we need is to
get pulled over by the cops.

15:38.420 --> 15:42.140
We need to get there, get a
boat, and find this painting.

15:42.140 --> 15:44.120
Time isn't on our side.

15:44.120 --> 15:46.490
I know it's wrapped up
pretty good, but eventually

15:46.490 --> 15:48.840
that seawater is going
to deteriorate it

15:48.840 --> 15:51.020
and then it's going to
cut into our profits.

15:51.020 --> 15:53.720
OK, step on it then.

15:53.720 --> 15:55.475
Hey, anyone here know
how to drive a boat?

15:59.080 --> 16:00.970
We'll worry about that
when we get there.

16:44.450 --> 16:46.190
This isn't a yacht.

16:46.190 --> 16:49.700
You two must be here for
the Top Model Tomorrow show.

16:49.700 --> 16:53.210
Which one of you is the model?

16:53.210 --> 16:55.850
She is, of course.

16:55.850 --> 16:58.850
Yeah, I was joking.

16:58.850 --> 17:01.600
Look, I'm sorry about the boat,
but that's all the station

17:01.600 --> 17:02.600
was going to spring for.

17:02.600 --> 17:03.770
But don't worry.

17:03.770 --> 17:05.150
We'll make it work.

17:05.150 --> 17:06.800
I'm Stan.

17:06.800 --> 17:10.880
This is Bree, your model,
and I'm Destiny, her manager.

17:10.880 --> 17:14.720
You don't plan on bringing all
that crap on board, do you?

17:14.720 --> 17:16.520
I need it for the shoot.

17:16.520 --> 17:17.960
Well, you can leave
it on the dock

17:17.960 --> 17:21.185
and we can come back and
pick it up if you need it.

17:21.185 --> 17:23.240
What if someone steals it?

17:23.240 --> 17:24.740
We can only be so lucky.

17:28.280 --> 17:29.630
It was another joke.

17:29.630 --> 17:32.510
You don't have much of a
sense of humor, do you, lady?

17:32.510 --> 17:34.880
Maybe your jokes just
aren't that funny.

17:34.880 --> 17:35.623
Fair enough.

17:35.623 --> 17:37.040
OK, here's what
we're going to do.

17:37.040 --> 17:38.873
We're going to shoot
some stuff on the boat,

17:38.873 --> 17:40.640
then we're going
to transmit live,

17:40.640 --> 17:42.410
then we're going to take
the boat out into the ocean

17:42.410 --> 17:43.745
and do some more B-roll footage.

17:46.470 --> 17:46.970
What?

17:46.970 --> 17:48.770
What's wrong now?

17:48.770 --> 17:52.130
Don't tell me you're
afraid of the water too.

17:52.130 --> 17:53.870
Well, she's just worried about--

17:53.870 --> 17:56.570
It's just all those stories
that your channel reports

17:56.570 --> 17:58.370
about the monster shark.

17:58.370 --> 18:00.500
Is it all true?

18:00.500 --> 18:01.820
Oh, yeah.

18:01.820 --> 18:08.450
As a matter of fact, it could be
lurking underwater right here!

18:08.450 --> 18:10.550
That was another joke, right?

18:10.550 --> 18:11.810
Look, don't worry.

18:11.810 --> 18:13.880
We're going to be
safe in the boat, OK?

18:13.880 --> 18:15.600
We have a lot of work to do.

18:15.600 --> 18:17.960
Now, there's a changing
room at the end of the pier.

18:17.960 --> 18:20.861
I'm going to start
getting set up, OK?

18:20.861 --> 18:23.330
OK, come on.

18:23.330 --> 18:25.382
This guy is so rude.

18:39.714 --> 18:45.150
I know you're out there, you
blood hungry son of a bitch.

18:50.370 --> 18:54.540
You and me have a
score to settle.

18:54.540 --> 18:55.920
[GROWLS]

18:56.840 --> 18:58.610
[SPLUTTERS]

19:04.681 --> 19:06.090
I hate the water!

19:14.960 --> 19:17.660
Jesus, ladies, this
isn't water ballet.

19:17.660 --> 19:18.740
What's wrong with this?

19:18.740 --> 19:19.730
The [INAUDIBLE]
contrasts perfectly

19:19.730 --> 19:20.813
with the blue ocean water.

19:20.813 --> 19:22.040
Yeah, I made it myself.

19:22.040 --> 19:24.830
And you call yourself a manager.

19:24.830 --> 19:25.520
Look, whatever.

19:25.520 --> 19:26.562
Come on, get in the boat.

19:32.450 --> 19:34.100
Miss America, you
stand right here.

19:34.100 --> 19:36.650
You, stay out of the way.

19:36.650 --> 19:38.180
OK, well, what do I do?

19:38.180 --> 19:40.760
OK, you're going to look
directly into the camera lens

19:40.760 --> 19:46.580
and answer every question that
the studio personnel ask you.

19:46.580 --> 19:48.935
You can formulate a
complete sentence, right?

19:51.480 --> 19:52.650
No, don't answer that.

19:52.650 --> 19:54.135
[CAMERA SNAPPING]

20:04.540 --> 20:07.860
Good afternoon, viewers, and
welcome to a special segment

20:07.860 --> 20:11.130
of Top Model Tomorrow,
where we find young women

20:11.130 --> 20:14.700
vying for the top spot in
today's fashion and modeling

20:14.700 --> 20:15.330
world.

20:15.330 --> 20:18.270
Live right now at
the marina we have up

20:18.270 --> 20:20.940
and coming model Bree Juare.

20:20.940 --> 20:24.540
