be in the modeling profession.

20:29.210 --> 20:33.000
Say something, dammit.

20:33.000 --> 20:33.855
We're live now?

20:33.855 --> 20:34.355
Yes.

20:38.650 --> 20:43.270
Well, it's wonderful to be on
your show and I'm so excited.

20:43.270 --> 20:45.200
What was the question again?

20:45.200 --> 20:48.250
Bree, why do you want
to be a top model?

20:48.250 --> 20:49.720
Oh, that's easy.

20:49.720 --> 20:51.610
For starters, I'm
very attractive.

20:51.610 --> 20:52.840
Anyone would agree with that.

20:52.840 --> 20:55.330
Plus my boyfriend thinks that
I should choose a profession

20:55.330 --> 20:56.770
where I keep my clothes on.

20:56.770 --> 20:58.507
Did you know a
female's shelf life

20:58.507 --> 20:59.965
on [INAUDIBLE] is
only three years?

21:02.830 --> 21:05.320
That's interesting, Bree.

21:05.320 --> 21:07.740
Tell us about your manager.

21:07.740 --> 21:09.580
Destiny?

21:09.580 --> 21:10.333
She's amazing.

21:10.333 --> 21:11.500
She's like my second mother.

21:11.500 --> 21:13.220
She takes such good care of me.

21:13.220 --> 21:15.880
I mean, she only does
take 60% of my earnings.

21:15.880 --> 21:17.590
I mean, that's so
generous of her.

21:33.620 --> 21:38.000
What is your vision
on world peace?

21:38.000 --> 21:40.340
I think everyone should get
a piece once in a while.

21:40.340 --> 21:42.035
No, no, no, not
that peace, Bree.

21:44.980 --> 21:47.065
Peace, getting along.

21:47.065 --> 21:48.040
Ah, yes.

21:48.040 --> 21:48.820
World peace.

21:52.280 --> 21:55.985
World peace is important so that
way the world can be peaceful.

21:58.530 --> 22:00.290
OK.

22:00.290 --> 22:02.400
Bree, tell us what else
we have to look forward

22:02.400 --> 22:04.620
to when we see you today?

22:04.620 --> 22:06.973
Well, in a few minutes we're
going to do a live fashion

22:06.973 --> 22:08.640
shoot right on this
boat, and then we're

22:08.640 --> 22:11.140
going to go out to the water
and take some more fun footage.

22:11.140 --> 22:13.080
I just hope--

22:13.080 --> 22:14.640
Well, what do you hope, Bree?

22:14.640 --> 22:16.890
I just hope that we don't
get attacked by that monster

22:16.890 --> 22:18.870
shark like the bank robbers.

22:18.870 --> 22:21.000
Painting thieves.

22:21.000 --> 22:23.640
I think you'll be
perfectly safe.

22:23.640 --> 22:25.590
Well, I hope.

22:25.590 --> 22:26.470
See you later.

22:26.470 --> 22:27.402
Ta-ta.

22:27.402 --> 22:29.500
We'll check in with you later.

22:29.500 --> 22:30.930
Good luck.

22:30.930 --> 22:32.070
Really.

22:32.070 --> 22:32.610
Good luck.

22:39.790 --> 22:42.970
I think we may have
found ourselves a boat.

22:42.970 --> 22:44.620
Hey, you two, let's go.

22:44.620 --> 22:45.120
Come on.

22:53.104 --> 22:56.597
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

23:55.980 --> 23:58.760
Let's take a look for a
moment at the recent events

23:58.760 --> 24:01.460
plaguing our seaside community.

24:01.460 --> 24:04.970
First we have the oil rig
that was recently destroyed

24:04.970 --> 24:07.400
last week by unknown causes.

24:07.400 --> 24:11.360
Then we have reports of a
mysterious, monstrous shark

24:11.360 --> 24:13.340
prowling the waters.

24:13.340 --> 24:16.280
Could the two
somehow be related?

24:16.280 --> 24:20.030
Calls to the headquarters to
the firm that owned and operated

24:20.030 --> 24:22.160
the rig have gone unanswered.

24:22.160 --> 24:24.980
However, we have a guest
in the studio today

24:24.980 --> 24:29.030
who may shed some light
on our shark mystery.

24:29.030 --> 24:31.160
Welcome to the
studio, Mr. Lennings.

24:31.160 --> 24:34.010
As difficult as it
must be, could you

24:34.010 --> 24:38.120
tell us a little bit about
your run-in with the shark?

24:38.120 --> 24:40.430
Well, I don't know
anything about that oil rig

24:40.430 --> 24:43.400
other than that it blocked
the view of the ocean we once

24:43.400 --> 24:46.580
had from the marina I managed.

24:46.580 --> 24:50.720
As far as the shark attack,
take a look at my legs!

24:50.720 --> 24:51.530
Zoom in.

24:51.530 --> 24:53.100
Go ahead.

24:53.100 --> 24:55.250
I don't have any!

24:55.250 --> 25:00.140
That's because a gigantic shark
bit them off in one fell swoop!

25:00.140 --> 25:03.800
I'm lucky I didn't
bleed to death.

25:03.800 --> 25:05.240
What kind of shark was it?

25:05.240 --> 25:07.970
A great white, mako?

25:07.970 --> 25:09.410
Neither.

25:09.410 --> 25:15.110
I know my sharks, and it
wasn't anything known to man.

25:15.110 --> 25:17.118
Where do you think it came from?

25:17.118 --> 25:17.660
I don't know.

25:17.660 --> 25:19.670
Maybe that rig with
all their drilling,

25:19.670 --> 25:21.260
they woke something up.

25:21.260 --> 25:24.710
All I know is nobody
is safe in the water

25:24.710 --> 25:27.400
until that thing is killed!

25:27.400 --> 25:30.590
If it isn't a known shark,
what do you think it could be?

25:30.590 --> 25:34.130
Oh, it is a shark all right.

25:34.130 --> 25:39.780
As far as what
species, who knows.

25:39.780 --> 25:42.330
Maybe it's the devil incarnate.

25:54.920 --> 25:56.130
You guys need anything?

25:56.130 --> 25:58.680
We're busy doing a
video shoot here.

25:58.680 --> 26:00.300
Who owns this rig?

26:00.300 --> 26:01.530
Nobody.

26:01.530 --> 26:03.820
The news station
rented it for the day.

26:03.820 --> 26:05.640
You see, we need to
head out to the channel

26:05.640 --> 26:07.170
there to look for something.

26:07.170 --> 26:09.450
We were hoping you'd be
neighborly and give us a lift.

26:09.450 --> 26:10.860
Yeah, I don't think so, pal.

26:10.860 --> 26:12.660
I got enough deadweight
on this boat.

26:16.030 --> 26:16.935
Oh, yes, you can.

26:25.770 --> 26:28.050
We tried to be
nice, but then you

26:28.050 --> 26:30.225
had to go and get
all snotty with us.

26:36.610 --> 26:38.405
What's this all about?

26:38.405 --> 26:40.405
Me, Boyd, and Clark are
looking for a painting--

26:40.405 --> 26:40.905
You idiot!

26:40.905 --> 26:42.640
You just give our names away!

26:42.640 --> 26:44.740
You guys are the painting
thieves everyone's

26:44.740 --> 26:46.370
looking for, right?

26:46.370 --> 26:48.040
Clever guess.

26:48.040 --> 26:50.110
Look, just take the keys and go.

26:50.110 --> 26:51.740
No, no can do.

26:51.740 --> 26:54.430
We need a driver and a couple
of hostages in case things

26:54.430 --> 26:55.120
heat up.

26:55.120 --> 26:57.283
Don't hurt us, please.

26:57.283 --> 26:58.200
What the hell is this?

26:58.200 --> 27:00.670
My grandmother wouldn't even
wear this terrible shit.

27:04.350 --> 27:05.370
What the hell was that?

27:05.370 --> 27:07.290
I thought I saw
something swim by.

27:07.290 --> 27:07.950
The shark!

27:07.950 --> 27:08.880
I knew it!

27:08.880 --> 27:10.290
Get me out of here!

27:10.290 --> 27:12.210
You're not going
anywhere, missy!

27:12.210 --> 27:14.250
You, get over here.

27:14.250 --> 27:16.420
I'll tell you when to stop.

27:16.420 --> 27:17.590
What about the shark?

27:17.590 --> 27:19.210
Enough about the shark.

27:19.210 --> 27:21.010
We're safe enough here.

27:21.010 --> 27:23.140
Just, everybody, be cool.

27:23.140 --> 27:25.510
You, no funny business.

27:25.510 --> 27:27.336
Understood.

27:27.336 --> 27:28.770
[BEEP]

28:41.930 --> 28:42.860
We're in business.

28:42.860 --> 28:44.480
Stop right here.

28:44.480 --> 28:45.200
If you insist.

28:56.430 --> 28:57.690
Doesn't work too good.

28:57.690 --> 28:59.670
Maybe it isn't
waterproof after all.

28:59.670 --> 29:01.080
It's just a fish or something.

29:05.160 --> 29:05.850
Wait a minute.

29:08.850 --> 29:10.183
I thought I saw something.

29:10.183 --> 29:11.100
Swing it to the right.

29:16.990 --> 29:17.980
Oh, jackpot.

29:17.980 --> 29:18.580
There it is.

29:18.580 --> 29:22.090
There's the painting
in the blue tarp.

29:22.090 --> 29:24.700
You sure are a
pretty little thing.

29:24.700 --> 29:28.000
I wouldn't mind being stranded
on a desert island with you.

29:28.000 --> 29:31.150
Leave her alone.

29:31.150 --> 29:31.800
[GUNSHOT]

29:31.800 --> 29:33.186
[GROANS]

29:35.040 --> 29:35.550
Oh, no!

29:35.550 --> 29:36.720
Help him!

29:36.720 --> 29:38.310
Why did you do that?

29:38.310 --> 29:39.225
He came at me!

29:42.410 --> 29:44.190
Shark!

29:44.190 --> 29:45.450
Help!

29:45.450 --> 29:46.232
[GROWLS]

29:46.232 --> 29:49.250
Help, help!

29:49.250 --> 29:50.990
We need to get the
hell out of here!

29:53.870 --> 29:55.310
[GASPING]

29:56.760 --> 29:57.810
We're not going anywhere!

29:57.810 --> 29:59.780
The painting's right beneath us!

29:59.780 --> 30:01.360
We're not going anywhere.

30:01.360 --> 30:02.870
What the hell is
she going on about?

30:02.870 --> 30:06.380
The man you just shot had
the keys in his pocket!

30:06.380 --> 30:08.210
I didn't know, I swear.

30:08.210 --> 30:10.280
And he came at me!

30:10.280 --> 30:12.180
Fucking great.

30:12.180 --> 30:13.100
Now what?

30:13.100 --> 30:14.330
We're stuck here.

30:14.330 --> 30:16.790
Look around, there's only water.

30:16.790 --> 30:18.598
Does anyone have a phone?

30:18.598 --> 30:20.390
You made us leave all
our bags at the dock,

30:20.390 --> 30:22.340
and our phones were in there.

30:22.340 --> 30:23.180
Fucking great.

30:35.060 --> 30:36.050
[SPLASH]

30:37.060 --> 30:37.720
There.

30:37.720 --> 30:40.210
At least we won't drift
away from the painting.

30:40.210 --> 30:41.710
What are we going to do?

30:41.710 --> 30:43.690
Give me a second to think.

30:43.690 --> 30:46.300
Remember, in 10 seconds
you ruined all our plans.

30:54.560 --> 30:56.355
What are you thinking?

30:56.355 --> 30:56.855
Nothing.

31:01.860 --> 31:02.950
Nothing at all.

31:02.950 --> 31:03.450
Good.

31:03.450 --> 31:04.350
Keep it that way.

31:08.820 --> 31:11.430
Tell us again about
your frightening escape

31:11.430 --> 31:14.400
from the doomed oil rig.

31:14.400 --> 31:17.680
My buddy and I had been
on the rig for months.

31:17.680 --> 31:21.660
I think they dug too deep
and discovered something.

31:21.660 --> 31:24.460
That's where I saw a large
prehistoric shark destroy

31:24.460 --> 31:26.100
our rig.

31:26.100 --> 31:28.140
No one stood a chance.

31:28.140 --> 31:31.080
What makes you believe
it was prehistoric?

31:31.080 --> 31:33.790
The secret operatives said so.

31:33.790 --> 31:35.670
They knew what it was.

31:35.670 --> 31:37.560
Tell us about the operatives.

31:37.560 --> 31:38.850
Who were they?

31:38.850 --> 31:42.630
They worked for the oil
company doing the drilling.

31:42.630 --> 31:46.500
We think they were sent here
to clean up all the witnesses.

31:46.500 --> 31:51.060
Another survivor and I
made it to Smash Up Island.

31:51.060 --> 31:53.070
There they captured
us and intended

31:53.070 --> 31:56.850
on killing us to silence
us so that we wouldn't

31:56.850 --> 31:59.670
say what we saw or knew.

31:59.670 --> 32:01.635
The shark got them,
though, and we escaped.

32:13.860 --> 32:15.330
Where the hell did his feed go?

32:27.690 --> 32:28.980
[SIGHS]

32:28.980 --> 32:29.820
Where is he?

32:42.540 --> 32:44.160
Boyd, see if you
can hotwire this

32:44.160 --> 32:46.030
while I keep an eye
on the painting.

32:46.030 --> 32:48.720
I don't know anything
about hot wiring a boat!

32:48.720 --> 32:50.100
I do.

32:50.100 --> 32:52.380
You want this idiot
to fry the engine out?

32:52.380 --> 32:54.705
Hey, hey, watch for your
calling an idiot, all right?

32:59.670 --> 33:02.670
Hey, you two, how long are
you supposed to be out here?

33:02.670 --> 33:03.480
Till this evening.

33:03.480 --> 33:04.065
Why?

33:04.065 --> 33:05.940
Just trying to figure
out how much time we've

33:05.940 --> 33:08.410
got before somebody
comes looking for us.

33:08.410 --> 33:11.050
We still have to
get our painting.

33:11.050 --> 33:12.890
I know.

33:12.890 --> 33:13.990
Whoa!

33:13.990 --> 33:16.900
What the hell?

33:16.900 --> 33:17.890
Out there!

33:17.890 --> 33:19.256
The shark!

33:19.256 --> 33:20.654
[GUNSHOTS]

33:23.920 --> 33:24.740
It's coming for us!

33:24.740 --> 33:25.240
Shoot!

33:28.140 --> 33:29.628
[GROWLS]

33:35.580 --> 33:37.152
Jesus, that was close.

33:37.152 --> 33:38.610
Did you see the
size of that thing?

33:38.610 --> 33:40.230
That wasn't no normal shark!

33:40.230 --> 33:42.480
What's important is that
it will be back for us!

33:42.480 --> 33:45.380
That thing has a vendetta
against us for some reason!

33:45.380 --> 33:46.940
Gerald, get back to hotwiring.

33:46.940 --> 33:49.400
And you, stop crying up there!

33:49.400 --> 33:51.400
We're safe enough!

33:51.400 --> 33:53.150
Until it capsizes us.

33:53.150 --> 33:54.770
Maybe so.

33:54.770 --> 33:56.810
Just hope you could swim faster.

33:56.810 --> 33:58.340
We're running out of time!

33:58.340 --> 34:00.170
And options.

34:00.170 --> 34:02.420
If I want anything
out of you, I'd ask.

34:02.420 --> 34:03.810
Get back to work.

34:03.810 --> 34:07.830
Maybe the Coast Guard will come
by soon and we'll be rescued.

34:07.830 --> 34:10.210
That's just what
they don't want.

34:10.210 --> 34:12.300
That's the smartest thing
you've said all day!

34:12.300 --> 34:13.770
Pipe down!

34:13.770 --> 34:15.878
I don't see it anywhere.

34:15.878 --> 34:16.920
It's out there somewhere.

34:16.920 --> 34:17.879
Keep your eyes peeled.

34:27.380 --> 34:30.620
Our investigative team
discovered crucial information

34:30.620 --> 34:32.750
in regards to the
oil rig disaster

34:32.750 --> 34:34.440
earlier this afternoon.

34:34.440 --> 34:37.070
It appears a large
bore S7 drill was

34:37.070 --> 34:40.639
used to puncture the bedrock
beneath the rig to drill deeper

34:40.639 --> 34:42.409
than anyone has before.

34:42.409 --> 34:45.860
Drilling regulations permit
only a size S2 drill.

34:45.860 --> 34:48.710
Could the illegal size drill
have fractured the foundation,

34:48.710 --> 34:50.719
causing the rig to collapse?

34:50.719 --> 34:52.790
Could the drill have
hit an ice pocket

34:52.790 --> 34:57.560
and released a sea demon
frozen in time into our oceans?

34:57.560 --> 35:01.610
An initial investigation by
authorities provides no clues.

35:01.610 --> 35:04.100
Another question
that goes unanswered

35:04.100 --> 35:06.950
is where did all the bodies go?

35:06.950 --> 35:09.860
Records show that 78
people worked on the rig

35:09.860 --> 35:11.390
on a daily basis.

35:11.390 --> 35:15.120
To this day, not one
body has been recovered.

35:15.120 --> 35:17.160
Did the tide wash
them out to sea,

35:17.160 --> 35:19.670
are they still trapped
in the wreckage,

35:19.670 --> 35:23.510
or did the so-called sea
monster devour them like flies

35:23.510 --> 35:25.530
as they fell into the water?

35:25.530 --> 35:27.890
These questions and
more will hopefully

35:27.890 --> 35:29.675
be answered in
the next few days.

35:37.520 --> 35:38.510
Well?

35:38.510 --> 35:40.400
This is impossible.

35:40.400 --> 35:41.537
Can't be repaired.

35:41.537 --> 35:43.120
I'm not sure if the
engine would start

35:43.120 --> 35:44.720
even if I could repair it.

35:44.720 --> 35:46.850
I told you he wouldn't
be able to get it going.

35:46.850 --> 35:49.850
This is coming from the asshole
who put us in this situation.

35:49.850 --> 35:51.942
Wait, let's just worry
about the painting.

35:51.942 --> 35:53.900
Maybe we have to paddle
this stinking thing out

35:53.900 --> 35:55.400
to Cat Island!

35:55.400 --> 35:57.680
Well, how can we recover it?

35:57.680 --> 35:59.900
One of us is going to dive in.

35:59.900 --> 36:01.468
Simple enough.

36:01.468 --> 36:02.510
Are you out of your mind?

36:02.510 --> 36:04.580
We won't last a minute
down there with that shark!

36:04.580 --> 36:05.480
The hell with the painting!

36:05.480 --> 36:06.710
Let's worry about our lives!

36:06.710 --> 36:08.390
Gerald, you're going in.

36:08.390 --> 36:09.440
The hell I am.

36:09.440 --> 36:12.020
You're the best swimmer here.

36:12.020 --> 36:13.100
You go, Boyd.

36:13.100 --> 36:15.470
You got us into this mess.

36:15.470 --> 36:17.810
Give me that.

36:17.810 --> 36:20.150
Empty.

36:20.150 --> 36:20.810
Come on, Clark.

36:20.810 --> 36:21.680
I'm not up to it.

36:21.680 --> 36:23.360
You don't have a choice.

36:23.360 --> 36:25.550
He'll die if you
send him down there.

36:25.550 --> 36:29.270
Maybe you'd like to
take his place then.

36:29.270 --> 36:30.800
Sharks are attracted to sound.

36:30.800 --> 36:33.200
What's that, Miss America?

36:33.200 --> 36:34.550
Sharks are attracted to sound.

36:34.550 --> 36:36.863
If we splash the water,
hit the side of the boat,

36:36.863 --> 36:38.780
hopefully it'll distract
the shark long enough

36:38.780 --> 36:40.550
for him to get down and back.

36:40.550 --> 36:42.425
No, I don't like the idea much.

36:51.780 --> 36:53.400
Look, it's directly below us.

36:53.400 --> 36:55.680
You dive down, grab
it, pull it up.

36:55.680 --> 36:57.730
It's only 18 feet
to the bottom here.

36:57.730 --> 36:59.070
You can do it.

36:59.070 --> 37:00.090
You think so, Clark?

37:00.090 --> 37:01.410
Yeah, just take a deep breath.

37:01.410 --> 37:02.430
You'll be fine.

37:02.430 --> 37:05.610
We'll be up here distracting it.

37:05.610 --> 37:07.760
OK.

37:07.760 --> 37:10.168
OK.

37:10.168 --> 37:10.710
Good, Gerald.

37:10.710 --> 37:11.210
Good.

37:11.210 --> 37:15.360
All right, let's start
hitting the boat.

37:15.360 --> 37:17.610
The water.

37:17.610 --> 37:20.360
Let's distract this mother!

37:20.360 --> 37:23.226
It's now or never.

37:23.226 --> 37:24.672
[THUMPING]

37:27.090 --> 37:27.810
Keep it up.

37:27.810 --> 37:29.850
Keep it up.

37:29.850 --> 37:30.630
It's working.

37:30.630 --> 37:32.550
The shark is circling the boat.

37:46.280 --> 37:48.084
Not good.

37:48.084 --> 37:49.575
[GROWLS]

38:20.450 --> 38:21.260
What's it doing?

38:26.890 --> 38:29.842
We're drifting.

38:29.842 --> 38:33.550
It snapped the anchor line.

38:33.550 --> 38:35.500
Shit!

38:35.500 --> 38:36.730
He didn't stand a chance.

38:39.410 --> 38:40.420
So much for that plan.

39:06.076 --> 39:07.564
[GROWLS]

39:11.532 --> 39:15.510
It's still out there
Why won't it go away?

39:15.510 --> 39:17.250
It has to at some point.

39:17.250 --> 39:18.480
And don't worry.

39:18.480 --> 39:20.250
Once we're overdue
to return, they'll

39:20.250 --> 39:22.030
send a search party out for us.

39:22.030 --> 39:24.300
We should be easy to spot.

39:24.300 --> 39:25.750
We don't even know where we are.

39:25.750 --> 39:28.890
We could have drifted miles
from where they even search.

39:28.890 --> 39:31.080
Well, we can't give up hope.

39:31.080 --> 39:34.380
We have to believe that they'll
search for us and find us.

39:34.380 --> 39:36.330
What about the shark?

39:36.330 --> 39:39.420
Well, maybe it has a
short attention span

39:39.420 --> 39:42.570
and will swim off.

39:42.570 --> 39:43.890
If we make it out of this--

39:43.890 --> 39:45.240
When we get out of this.

39:45.240 --> 39:46.020
When.

39:46.020 --> 39:48.390
When we make it out
of this, I don't even

39:48.390 --> 39:50.130
care about being top model.

39:50.130 --> 39:51.120
I just want to live.

39:54.460 --> 39:57.370
I want some more of that.

39:57.370 --> 40:01.430
Well, you don't get any more.

40:01.430 --> 40:03.530
What about them?

40:03.530 --> 40:05.435
Well, I think
we're safe for now.

40:13.730 --> 40:15.050
Bastard!

40:15.050 --> 40:17.310
Why doesn't it
just finish us off?

40:17.310 --> 40:19.010
It's toying with us.

40:19.010 --> 40:22.070
It knows it's got us
where it wants us.

40:22.070 --> 40:24.251
Predators do that, you know.

40:24.251 --> 40:26.660
They relish in the torture.

40:26.660 --> 40:28.970
Instant kill is too easy.

40:28.970 --> 40:34.400
Speaking of an easy kill,
what we do about these two?

40:34.400 --> 40:37.730
I've been thinking about that.

40:37.730 --> 40:40.760
They would make good shark
food if it came to it.

40:40.760 --> 40:42.520
I agree.

40:42.520 --> 40:45.010
Either way, we
can't let them go.

40:45.010 --> 40:49.240
They know our names,
our faces, our plan.

40:49.240 --> 40:51.790
When the time comes,
we'll deal with them.

40:51.790 --> 40:53.680
And the painting?

40:53.680 --> 40:56.050
At least we know
where the location is.

40:56.050 --> 40:58.510
We'll come back once we
get out of this shit.

40:58.510 --> 41:00.395
OK, Clark.

