Huh?

43:06.870 --> 43:08.970
You want to have
some fucking fun?

43:08.970 --> 43:10.746
Come on!

43:10.746 --> 43:12.240
[GROWLS]

43:13.236 --> 43:14.232
Let me go!

43:18.730 --> 43:20.890
Fucking next time I
will end your ass!

43:20.890 --> 43:22.220
[COUGHING]

43:25.130 --> 43:25.870
Stop!

43:25.870 --> 43:26.440
Clark!

43:26.440 --> 43:27.160
Stop it!

43:30.520 --> 43:32.950
Oh, god!

43:32.950 --> 43:35.080
Next time I'll fucking end you!

44:04.750 --> 44:05.935
Land nowhere in sight.

44:10.410 --> 44:14.110
You're a smart one, pushing us
out to the sea in this current.

44:19.310 --> 44:20.734
[GUNSHOTS]

44:21.234 --> 44:22.677
[GRUNTS ANGRILY]

44:25.570 --> 44:29.340
Eat lead for breakfast!

44:29.340 --> 44:30.645
I hate this shark!

44:40.580 --> 44:41.910
Good morning, everyone.

44:41.910 --> 44:45.300
Our top story this hour is
the Top Model contestant,

44:45.300 --> 44:48.750
her manager, and our own
cameraman reported missing

44:48.750 --> 44:50.430
and thought to be lost at sea.

44:50.430 --> 44:53.220
A boat malfunction is
thought to be the cause,

44:53.220 --> 44:55.800
and, as we reported
yesterday live,

44:55.800 --> 44:58.860
the Top Model Tomorrow
show went on location

44:58.860 --> 45:01.860
to the sand and surf
for a special show.

45:01.860 --> 45:03.645
After the live
feed at noon, they

45:03.645 --> 45:06.900
were both headed out to
sea for another segment.

45:06.900 --> 45:11.160
Contact since then has been
lost, with recovery operations

45:11.160 --> 45:12.420
underway.

45:12.420 --> 45:15.030
A search and rescue
team headed by the Navy

45:15.030 --> 45:16.500
commenced an hour ago.

45:16.500 --> 45:20.220
We will keep you updated
as we receive information.

46:13.613 --> 46:15.609
[RADAR PINGING]

46:40.559 --> 46:41.971
Do you guys hear that?

46:41.971 --> 46:43.054
[DISTANT HELICOPTER ROTOR]

46:43.054 --> 46:44.205
Hear what?

46:46.920 --> 46:50.010
The sun must be frying
your brain, girlie.

46:50.010 --> 46:53.430
I don't hear anything.

46:53.430 --> 46:54.720
Sounds like a helicopter.

46:54.720 --> 46:57.090
Maybe a search party.

46:57.090 --> 46:59.810
You're imagining things.

46:59.810 --> 47:00.770
Yeah, must be.

47:04.480 --> 47:05.440
Over there, land!

47:10.340 --> 47:12.140
Do you think it's Cat Island?

47:12.140 --> 47:13.250
I can't tell.

47:13.250 --> 47:14.090
It has to be.

47:14.090 --> 47:15.620
There's nothing
else around here.

47:15.620 --> 47:17.540
Either way, we have
to get off this water

47:17.540 --> 47:20.240
and onto some dry land.

47:20.240 --> 47:23.180
What do we do?

47:23.180 --> 47:23.735
We'll paddle.

47:26.380 --> 47:27.290
Here you go.

47:30.370 --> 47:32.370
Up front.

47:32.370 --> 47:32.870
Gosh.

48:12.112 --> 48:13.180
[GRUNTS]

48:13.180 --> 48:15.970
The current seems
to be in our favor.

48:15.970 --> 48:19.090
Stop wasting your energy
and stop jabbering.

48:19.090 --> 48:20.590
Just paddle!

48:20.590 --> 48:22.225
I knew we'd make
it through this!

48:22.225 --> 48:23.448
[LAUGHS]

48:24.855 --> 48:26.262
[SCREAMS]

48:27.470 --> 48:27.970
Boyd!

48:27.970 --> 48:29.020
No!

48:29.020 --> 48:30.502
[SCREAMS]

48:31.490 --> 48:32.472
Help!

48:32.472 --> 48:32.972
Help!

48:43.850 --> 48:44.465
Good riddance.

48:49.230 --> 48:50.100
Keep paddling.

48:50.100 --> 48:53.220
We don't have time to mourn.

48:53.220 --> 48:55.000
I wouldn't anyway.

48:55.000 --> 48:57.485
And then there were two.

48:57.485 --> 48:59.120
Huh?

48:59.120 --> 49:01.560
It's just you and I now.

49:01.560 --> 49:04.280
Yeah, until you
decide to kill me.

49:04.280 --> 49:07.750
No, you've got a pretty
good arm over there.

49:07.750 --> 49:09.210
And when we get to the island?

49:09.210 --> 49:11.550
That's if we get to the island.

49:11.550 --> 49:13.335
If we get to the island?

49:13.335 --> 49:15.780
We'll just go our separate ways.

49:15.780 --> 49:18.750
Look, I don't want to
harm you or anybody.

49:18.750 --> 49:21.480
Didn't seem that way, did it?

49:21.480 --> 49:25.830
Life doesn't always
turn out how you plan.

49:25.830 --> 49:26.790
It's funny like that.

49:26.790 --> 49:28.350
You'll see.

49:28.350 --> 49:31.950
You think I always wanted
to be a petty crook?

49:31.950 --> 49:35.060
Then why did you?

49:35.060 --> 49:35.900
It is what it is.

49:35.900 --> 49:37.250
I'll own it.

49:37.250 --> 49:39.050
It's my own doing.

49:39.050 --> 49:39.843
Look, you're young.

49:39.843 --> 49:41.510
You've got your whole
life ahead of you.

49:41.510 --> 49:42.365
Mine's over.

49:45.686 --> 49:47.174
[HELICOPTER ROTOR]

49:52.150 --> 49:53.800
Don't tell me I'm
imagining that.

49:53.800 --> 49:56.700
You don't hear that?

49:56.700 --> 49:58.050
It looks like a copter.

49:58.050 --> 49:59.235
Maybe it's a Navy chopper.

50:02.640 --> 50:03.150
Finally.

50:03.150 --> 50:04.824
We'll be saved.

50:04.824 --> 50:08.400
Hey, over here!

50:08.400 --> 50:09.150
Wonderful.

50:09.150 --> 50:10.800
25 years in the big house.

50:10.800 --> 50:13.804
Yeah, wonderful.

50:13.804 --> 50:14.650
Over here.

50:14.650 --> 50:15.365
Hey!

50:15.365 --> 50:17.490
Over here.

50:17.490 --> 50:18.370
They've seen us.

50:18.370 --> 50:19.030
We're saved.

51:02.370 --> 51:03.650
It's not looking good.

51:03.650 --> 51:05.900
I think we have
ourselves a big problem.

51:05.900 --> 51:07.470
What's the problem, Clark?

51:07.470 --> 51:08.920
Yeah, the painting's missing.

51:08.920 --> 51:11.390
But none of that can
be traced back to us.

51:11.390 --> 51:13.340
Not yet anyways.

51:13.340 --> 51:17.630
I knew these guys were
going to fumble up this job.

51:17.630 --> 51:21.380
All they had to do was
meet us on Cat Island,

51:21.380 --> 51:23.330
give us the painting,
they get their cut,

51:23.330 --> 51:25.280
and then we get our cut.

51:25.280 --> 51:25.895
It was simple.

51:32.874 --> 51:35.750
You sure are pretty.

51:35.750 --> 51:39.160
I wouldn't mind being stranded
on a desert island with you.

51:39.160 --> 51:42.240
Leave her alone.

51:42.240 --> 51:42.740
[GUNSHOT]

51:42.740 --> 51:44.182
[GASPS]

51:46.170 --> 51:47.910
Oh, no, help him!

51:47.910 --> 51:49.440
Why did you do that?

51:49.440 --> 51:50.280
He came at me!

51:53.316 --> 51:55.630
Shark!

51:55.630 --> 51:57.010
Help!

51:57.010 --> 51:57.920
Help, help!

52:00.650 --> 52:02.464
We need to get the
hell out of here!

52:07.760 --> 52:08.940
We're not going anywhere!

52:08.940 --> 52:10.940
The painting's right beneath us!

52:10.940 --> 52:12.500
We're not going anywhere.

52:12.500 --> 52:14.000
What the hell is
she going on about?

52:14.000 --> 52:17.520
The man you just shot had
the keys in his pocket!

52:17.520 --> 52:19.380
I didn't know, I swear.

52:19.380 --> 52:21.390
And he came at me!

52:21.390 --> 52:22.200
Fucking great.

52:28.601 --> 52:32.120
You certainly are a
pretty little thing.

52:32.120 --> 52:33.410
What do you want?

52:33.410 --> 52:34.560
Don't be afraid.

52:34.560 --> 52:38.466
You and I, we're going
to be real good friends.

52:38.466 --> 52:39.890
Stop!

52:39.890 --> 52:40.390
Hey!

52:40.390 --> 52:42.320
Let go of her!

52:42.320 --> 52:43.840
Back off, lady!

52:43.840 --> 52:46.141
Her and I were having some fun!

52:46.141 --> 52:47.614
[YELLS]

52:50.069 --> 52:51.051
Destiny!

52:51.051 --> 52:52.033
Help me!

52:55.961 --> 52:57.925
Grab my arm!

52:57.925 --> 53:00.540
What the hell are you doing?

53:00.540 --> 53:02.000
[GROWLS]

53:02.500 --> 53:03.960
It got me!

53:03.960 --> 53:04.460
Help!

53:04.460 --> 53:05.440
It's coming!

53:05.440 --> 53:06.420
Help!

53:06.420 --> 53:07.890
Help me!

53:07.890 --> 53:09.360
[GROWLS]

53:18.670 --> 53:20.140
What the hell are you doing?

53:20.140 --> 53:21.120
She interrupted us!

53:21.120 --> 53:22.590
We were having fun!

53:22.590 --> 53:23.600
Who cares?

53:23.600 --> 53:25.640
We were going to
kill them anyway.

53:25.640 --> 53:26.810
I'll show you fun.

53:33.642 --> 53:36.170
You having fun?

53:36.170 --> 53:38.025
Having fun yet?

53:38.025 --> 53:38.780
Huh?

53:38.780 --> 53:40.800
You want to have
some fucking fun?

53:40.800 --> 53:42.570
Come on!

53:42.570 --> 53:44.055
[GROWLS]

53:45.045 --> 53:46.035
Pull me out!

53:50.490 --> 53:54.150
The fucking next time
I will end your ass!

53:54.150 --> 53:55.210
[COUGHS]

53:56.533 --> 53:57.856
Oh, stop!

53:57.856 --> 53:59.020
Clark, stop it!

54:02.492 --> 54:04.770
Oh, god!

54:04.770 --> 54:07.140
Next time I'll fucking end you!

54:13.840 --> 54:15.690
What happened?

54:15.690 --> 54:16.480
You hit your head.

54:16.480 --> 54:18.640
You've been out
cold for a while.

54:18.640 --> 54:20.020
I guess I fell asleep too.

54:23.120 --> 54:25.430
No more rescue copters?

54:25.430 --> 54:26.270
No.

54:26.270 --> 54:31.220
Not going to be one
for a while, if that.

54:31.220 --> 54:34.070
You think we should keep
paddling out to the island?

54:34.070 --> 54:39.470
We should, but I think
we've drifted farther away.

54:39.470 --> 54:41.900
Where do you think it is?

54:41.900 --> 54:42.650
Not far.

54:42.650 --> 54:44.750
Probably beneath us.

54:44.750 --> 54:46.730
Yeah, that's what I thought.

54:46.730 --> 54:48.920
It won't give up.

54:48.920 --> 54:51.770
Never realized
sharks held grudges.

54:51.770 --> 54:55.100
I mean, they are the
oldest living species.

54:55.100 --> 54:58.100
They've gone through hundreds
of millions of years of change.

54:58.100 --> 55:01.310
There's probably so much that
humans will never understand.

55:01.310 --> 55:03.260
We can never make it
a fraction as far.

55:06.800 --> 55:08.960
Hey, there it is.

55:08.960 --> 55:11.450
It's trying to prevent us
from getting to the island.

55:11.450 --> 55:13.640
How the hell does
it know our plans?

55:13.640 --> 55:14.975
A shark can't be that smart.

55:17.830 --> 55:19.318
[GROWLS]

55:26.270 --> 55:27.800
What should we do?

55:27.800 --> 55:30.080
What's a shark's weak point?

55:30.080 --> 55:34.190
Uh, a normal shark,
it's above the eye.

55:34.190 --> 55:37.680
If you puncture that, it'll
pierce the brain cavity.

55:37.680 --> 55:39.350
Then that's what we need to do.

55:39.350 --> 55:41.120
I said a normal shark.

55:41.120 --> 55:42.800
This is not a normal shark.

55:42.800 --> 55:43.970
We have to try.

55:43.970 --> 55:45.620
Look for something
sharp or pointed.

55:57.600 --> 55:58.100
Bingo.

56:04.490 --> 56:05.630
Raise some hell.

56:05.630 --> 56:08.450
Make some noise to distract it.

56:08.450 --> 56:09.350
There it is.

56:09.350 --> 56:10.910
Come on, you big ugly fish!

56:10.910 --> 56:14.030
Take this!

56:14.030 --> 56:16.520
Come on!

56:16.520 --> 56:17.270
Come on!

56:20.678 --> 56:21.680
Come on!

56:26.426 --> 56:27.878
[GROWLS]

56:27.878 --> 56:29.838
What the hell just happened?

56:29.838 --> 56:30.380
I don't know.

56:30.380 --> 56:31.250
What is that?

56:31.250 --> 56:33.670
Another shark?

56:33.670 --> 56:36.090
I don't know.

56:36.090 --> 56:37.542
Something bad's about to happen.

56:37.542 --> 56:38.994
[GROWLING]

56:41.362 --> 56:43.950
Well, that solves one problem.

56:43.950 --> 56:46.340
Yeah, but now we have another.

56:46.340 --> 56:48.290
Where do you think
that came from?

56:48.290 --> 56:50.450
Someone's nightmare.

56:50.450 --> 56:53.720
It looked homemade,
stitched together.

56:53.720 --> 56:56.300
I know what that is.

56:56.300 --> 56:58.220
Go on.

56:58.220 --> 56:59.540
That's Sharkenstein.

56:59.540 --> 57:00.500
Sharken what?

57:00.500 --> 57:02.900
You never heard of the
legend of Sharkenstein?

57:02.900 --> 57:04.160
No.

57:04.160 --> 57:05.690
I guess I'm about to.

57:05.690 --> 57:07.490
Legend has it a
Nazi scientist who

57:07.490 --> 57:11.060
lived offshore was experimenting
with Frankenstein's heart

57:11.060 --> 57:14.540
and brain and successfully
transplanted it into a shark.

57:14.540 --> 57:15.710
It has to be it.

57:15.710 --> 57:17.690
A tad far fetched,
wouldn't you say?

57:17.690 --> 57:21.320
Sure, as believable as being
stalked by a prehistoric shark.

57:21.320 --> 57:23.150
Why is it here now?

57:23.150 --> 57:27.380
It was supposedly destroyed,
but it appears it survived.

57:27.380 --> 57:30.390
We should get to Cat Island.

57:30.390 --> 57:32.120
Clark, watch out.

57:32.120 --> 57:33.560
[GROWLS]

57:39.320 --> 57:40.145
Now's my chance.

58:18.789 --> 58:21.220
I made it.

58:21.220 --> 58:23.230
I made it.

58:23.230 --> 58:24.235
You can't get me now.

58:26.975 --> 58:28.448
[GROWLS]

58:29.430 --> 58:32.505
This can't be good.

58:32.505 --> 58:33.990
Like, really?

58:33.990 --> 58:35.475
This is happening?

59:04.544 --> 59:08.655
You will stay down.

59:08.655 --> 59:10.080
[GROWLING]

59:14.840 --> 59:16.852
Surprised to see me, my friend?

59:31.150 --> 59:34.260
I'm so glad that you came along.

59:34.260 --> 59:35.406
Maybe.

59:35.406 --> 59:36.105
Maybe not.

59:38.675 --> 59:40.445
You will come with me.

59:59.450 --> 01:00:02.810
You would not believe
the day I've had.

01:00:02.810 --> 01:00:06.530
I am not interested
in your problems.

01:00:06.530 --> 01:00:10.090
Let me guess, you're
the mad scientist.

01:00:10.090 --> 01:00:14.620
I am Klaus, a genius,
working to further

01:00:14.620 --> 01:00:15.925
the interests of my fuhrer.

01:00:20.100 --> 01:00:24.555
So the Nazi mad scientist, and
you've kept Hitler's brain.

01:00:28.190 --> 01:00:31.220
You no doubt have heard about
the legendary accomplishments

01:00:31.220 --> 01:00:34.880
of myself and my creation.

01:00:34.880 --> 01:00:36.960
Not exactly.

01:00:36.960 --> 01:00:38.450
Then let me educate you.

01:00:41.260 --> 01:00:43.270
I knew that was coming.

01:00:43.270 --> 01:00:45.010
I am Klaus.

01:00:45.010 --> 01:00:48.190
Said creature is
Sharkenstein, decades

01:00:48.190 --> 01:00:50.620
worth of experimentation.

01:00:50.620 --> 01:00:54.220
I will use it to continue
the reign of my fuhrer.

01:00:54.220 --> 01:00:58.810
His brain will ultimately be
transplanted into someone.

01:00:58.810 --> 01:01:02.450
Maybe even you.

01:01:02.450 --> 01:01:03.310
I'll pass.

01:01:03.310 --> 01:01:05.470
Thanks, though.

01:01:05.470 --> 01:01:09.250
You would not be
wise to doubt me.

01:01:09.250 --> 01:01:11.590
Seems like your pet needs
some obedience lessons.

01:01:15.480 --> 01:01:20.190
It escaped and injured me,
but we will recapture it

01:01:20.190 --> 01:01:24.010
and my experiments
will continue.

01:01:24.010 --> 01:01:27.985
I've had enough of sharks in
the last two days, so I'm good.

01:01:27.985 --> 01:01:29.610
I think I'm just
going to hitch a ride.

01:01:29.610 --> 01:01:31.305
You got a phone or something?

01:01:34.770 --> 01:01:36.860
You will not be going anywhere.

01:01:45.526 --> 01:01:46.990
[GROWLING]

01:01:56.760 --> 01:02:00.020
So what's the
plan, Von Rickards?

01:02:00.020 --> 01:02:01.250
It's Klaus.

01:02:01.250 --> 01:02:04.280
The name is Klaus.

01:02:04.280 --> 01:02:05.900
Keep your swastika on, pal.

01:02:05.900 --> 01:02:07.870
I was only joking.

01:02:07.870 --> 01:02:10.070
This is no laughing matter.

01:02:10.070 --> 01:02:13.970
A new world order is at hand,
and you are lucky enough

01:02:13.970 --> 01:02:15.380
to be a part of it.

01:02:18.510 --> 01:02:20.992
No more exciting than being
on Top Model Tomorrow.

01:02:20.992 --> 01:02:22.200
Have you ever seen that show?

01:02:24.940 --> 01:02:27.490
Klaus does not watch
saccharine-coated TV

01:02:27.490 --> 01:02:30.660
programming.

01:02:30.660 --> 01:02:31.950
You should get out more.

01:02:31.950 --> 01:02:34.530
What are you even
fiddling with here?

01:02:34.530 --> 01:02:38.040
I'm making fine
adjustments to my stun gun

01:02:38.040 --> 01:02:41.940
so next time we meet the
shark, it will not escape.

01:02:41.940 --> 01:02:46.530
I will stun it with this and you
and I will bring it back here

01:02:46.530 --> 01:02:49.170
for modifications and
further experimenting.

01:02:52.040 --> 01:02:56.950
Probably an answer I don't
want, but what about me?

01:02:56.950 --> 01:03:00.910
You will be safe as
long as you help me.

01:03:00.910 --> 01:03:04.880
Then I will release you.

01:03:04.880 --> 01:03:09.100
And how do you plan on
finding this Sharkenstein?

01:03:09.100 --> 01:03:10.390
It will find us.

01:03:24.510 --> 01:03:28.410
When I said help, I didn't
exactly have this in mind.

01:03:28.410 --> 01:03:29.940
The shark knows you.

01:03:29.940 --> 01:03:31.590
It has marked you.

01:03:31.590 --> 01:03:34.620
Once it gets your
scent, it will be here.

01:03:34.620 --> 01:03:38.040
Then I will jump
out and stun it.

01:03:38.040 --> 01:03:40.440
Don't be taking
your time with that.

01:03:40.440 --> 01:03:42.360
One last question.

01:03:42.360 --> 01:03:44.490
What is it now?

01:03:44.490 --> 01:03:48.120
How exactly will
it get my scent?

01:03:48.120 --> 01:03:49.260
Glad you asked.

01:04:00.370 --> 01:04:02.365
It won't be long now, young one.

01:04:08.840 --> 01:04:10.770
Where is that blasted beast?

01:04:20.016 --> 01:04:21.984
[ANIMAL PANTING]

01:04:26.412 --> 01:04:27.888
[SCREAMS]

01:04:30.850 --> 01:04:32.930
It's that girl and
her silly screaming.

01:04:37.390 --> 01:04:38.900
Welcome back, my pet.

01:04:44.780 --> 01:04:46.580
The damn sight must be off.

01:04:51.470 --> 01:04:52.687
I will not be defeated!

01:04:55.669 --> 01:04:58.154
Feets, don't fail me now.

01:05:09.088 --> 01:05:10.579
[GROWLS]

01:05:31.520 --> 01:05:32.350
Hell, yeah.

01:05:58.298 --> 01:06:00.762
Look at this.

01:06:00.762 --> 01:06:02.250
[GROWLS]

01:06:08.698 --> 01:06:10.186
Is that all you've got?

01:06:20.106 --> 01:06:21.594
[SHARK GROWLS]

01:06:42.460 --> 01:06:45.000
Is it over?

01:06:45.000 --> 01:06:46.395
Is it really over?

01:07:00.183 --> 01:07:03.177
[SINISTER MUSIC]

01:07:06.171 --> 01:07:10.914
[MUSIC PLAYING]
